  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 47a621783cb453147b01764dde5ed130, type: 3}
  m_Name: AFavorForTheBlacksmith
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::NPCDialogue
  dialogueLines:
  - There you are.
  - Been meaning to check on the cottage since you moved in.
  - Place has good bones, but it's falling apart in spots.
  - If you're planning to stay long-term, you'll need proper tools.
  - Lucky for you, I had a few old ones lying around.
  - The axe is for chopping trees, and the pickaxe will break small boulders.
  - Bring me some wood and stone when you've gathered enough. It'll be good practice.
  - Tools only get useful once you've got dirt on them.
  - Keep gathering. You'll need plenty of materials around here anyway.
  - Good haul. Most newcomers swing an axe like they're fighting it.
  - You're getting the hang of things faster than I expected.
  - Keep collecting materials when you can.
  - Around here, fixing one thing usually means repairing three more...
  - A sharp tool and steady hands solve most problems.
  - The rest just takes time.
